What’s the deal with the Fountain of Magical Brethren in the Ministry of Magic?  At first glance, the golden statue of a wizard, witch, centaur, goblin, and house-elf looks like a symbol of unity. But a closer look reveals it’s actually a glittering facade — a convenient lie about equality in the wizarding world.
